-- Land Rover Appointed Sponsor of Next Two Rugby World Cups in 2011, 2015
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2010-11-24T12:09:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-24/land-rover-appointed-sponsor-of-next-two-rugby-world-cups-in-2011-2015.html
Land Rover was appointed an official
sponsor of Rugby World Cup 2011 in New Zealand and a top-level
worldwide partner of the following edition of the event in
England in 2015.  As part of the agreement, Land Rover will supply vehicles
to support the organizers, teams and officials at the events.
It’s the first time the manufacturer has been involved with the
tournament.  Luxury-SUV maker Land Rover is part of  Tata Motors Ltd .’s
Jaguar Land Rover brand.  The Rugby World Cup announced the sponsorship in a
 statement on its website , without giving financial terms.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  